'''墨西哥毒品戰爭'''（{{Lang-es|Guerra contra el narcotráfico en México}}）是[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]從2006年12月11日起至2019年1月30日，販毒集團之間或贩毒集团與墨西哥政府之間進行的[[低強度戰爭|低强度]]的[[非对称作战|非对称作战]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mexican citizens take the drug war into their own hands|url=https://theworld.org/stories/2014-01-16/mexican-citizens-frustrated-their-government-take-arms-against-drug-cartel|access-date=2021-12-11|work=The World from PRX|language=en|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211064947/https://theworld.org/stories/2014-01-16/mexican-citizens-frustrated-their-government-take-arms-against-drug-cartel|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/programmes/faultlines/2011/06/201162174315458265.html |title=Mexico's hidden war – Fault Lines – Al Jazeera English |access-date=2014-12-07 |archive-date=2020-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414010454/https://www.aljazeera.com/programmes/faultlines/2011/06/201162174315458265.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=U.S. Special Forces Trained Mexican Troops in Colorado|url=https://insightcrime.org/news/brief/us-special-forces-trained-mexican-troops-in-colorado/|access-date=2021-12-11|date=2011-08-11|work=InSight Crime|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211201138/https://insightcrime.org/news/brief/us-special-forces-trained-mexican-troops-in-colorado/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=The Mexican Drug Wars: Organized Crime, Narco-Terrorism, Insurgency or Asymmetric Warfare?|url=http://citation.allacademic.com/meta/p_mla_apa_research_citation/5/1/2/4/2/p512428_index.html|access-date=2014-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626104137/http://citation.allacademic.com/meta/p_mla_apa_research_citation/5/1/2/4/2/p512428_index.html|archive-date=2015-06-26|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。墨西哥政府宣稱，它的目標主要是遏止販毒集團之間的暴力事件，<ref>{{cite news|title=ANUNCIO SOBRE LA OPERACIÓN CONJUNTA MICHOACÁN|url=http://www.presidencia.gob.mx/2006/12/anuncio-sobre-la-operacion-conjunta-michoacan/|newspaper=Presidencia de la Republica, Mexico|date=11 dic 2006|accessdate=2011-10-04|archive-date=2019-06-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190619182400/http://www.presidencia.gob.mx/2006/12/anuncio-sobre-la-operacion-conjunta-michoacan/|dead-url=no}}</ref>以及瓦解強大的販毒集團，阻止毒品販運則在次要，後者主要留給[[美國|美國]]政府處理。<ref>{{cite news|title=Calderón: Estamos luchando en contra de los criminales|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cqohiZCVwv0&feature=feedwll&list=WL|newspaper=TeleSur TV|date=2011-08-30|accessdate=2011-10-04|archive-date=2017-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120185614/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cqohiZCVwv0&feature=feedwll&list=WL|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Poiré defiende estrategia del Gobierno Federal en lucha antinarco; entrevista AlJazeera|url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T9WgqD04niE|newspaper=AlJazeera News|date=2011-08-18|accessdate=2011-10-04|archive-date=2020-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414010519/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T9WgqD04niE|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Sugiere Sarukhán que Calderón no busca reducir tráfico de drogas|url=http://sdpnoticias.com/nota/71635/Sugiere_Sarukhan_que_Calderon_no_busca_reducir_trafico_de_drogas|newspaper=SDP Noticias|date=2011-05-17|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020022706/http://www.sdpnoticias.com/nota/71635/Sugiere_Sarukhan_que_Calderon_no_busca_reducir_trafico_de_drogas|archivedate=2014-10-20}}</ref>

墨西哥販毒集團已有數十年的歷史，而发展壮大则是到1990年代[[哥倫比亞|哥倫比亞]]的卡利及[[巴勃羅·埃斯科瓦爾|麥德林販毒集團]]衰落之後。墨西哥販毒集團現在已經主导了美國的毒品批發市場。<ref name="Cook7">{{Cite book|contribution=Mexico's Drug Cartels|title=CRS Report for Congress|editor-first=Colleen W.|editor-last=Cook|publisher=Congressional Research Service|place=|page=7|date=October 16|year=2007|contribution-url=http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/row/RL34215.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=2009-08-09|archive-date=2008-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080516053805/http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/row/RL34215.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>同时，对一些販毒集團頭目的抓捕引發了更多毒品暴力，販毒集團之间為了爭奪进入美國的运毒路线的控制權而不斷衝突。<ref name="progress">{{cite news|author=TRACI CARL|title=Progress in Mexico drug war is drenched in blood|date=2009-11-03|publisher=INSI|url=http://www.newssafety.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=12194:progress-in-mexico-drug-war-is-drenched-in-blood&catid=345:mexico-security&Itemid=100298|agency=Associated Press|accessdate=2010-03-16|archive-date=2014-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202121843/http://www.newssafety.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=12194:progress-in-mexico-drug-war-is-drenched-in-blood&catid=345:mexico-security&Itemid=100298|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=High U.S. cocaine cost shows drug war working: Mexico|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mexico-drugs-idUSN1422771920070914|newspaper=Reuters|date=2007-09-14|accessdate=2021-12-11|language=en|archive-date=2017-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812212903/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mexico-drugs-idUSN1422771920070914|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|contribution=CRS Report for Congress|title=Mexico - U.S. Relations: Issues for Congress|editor-first=Mark P.|editor-last=Sullivan|publisher=Congressional Research Service|pages=2, 13, 14|date=2008-12-18|contribution-url=http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/row/RL32724.pdf|accessdate=2009-04-01|10=|archive-date=2010-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100610113341/http://www.fas.org/sgp/crs/row/RL32724.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[美國司法部|美國司法部]]估計非法毒品交易帶來的批發收益全年介乎136億至484億美元之間<ref name=Cook7 /><ref name="spread">{{Cite news|title=Mexican drug gangs 'spread in US'|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/8588509.stm|date=2010-03-26|accessdate=2021-12-11|language=en-GB|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126063728/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/8588509.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Ashley|last=Fantz|title=The Mexico drug war: Bodies for billions|date=2012-01-20|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/01/15/world/mexico-drug-war-essay/index.html|publisher=CNN News|accessdate=2012-03-05|archive-date=2012-12-09|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CmDgNIfS?url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/01/15/world/mexico-drug-war-essay/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而且總量還在增加中，兩國吸毒市場近四千萬人，甚至猜測可以達到近千億美元的天文數字，造成大量的外匯流失。而且又因為美國是世界最大的槍械彈藥製造國，搭配上南美的武裝走私，在墨國的富有黑幫中造成槍枝嚴重氾濫的治安問題。

